node.text:
Now that summer is over, it’s the perfect time to set new routines. 🌟

Total Body Guide, my exclusive fitness and nutrition program, is now OPEN for enrollment!! 🥳🥳 And this time… we’re getting FIT FOR FALL!! 🍁🌞🍂

Get ready for 21 days of workouts, healthy fall- inspired meals, community, accountability coaching and weekly check-ins with ME, your Coach!! 💝

I take ALL the guesswork out of what and when to eat, how to workout and how to create small goals that drive MAJOR MOMENTUM.⚡️ 

Plus, with my Fit for Fall Bundle, I’ll send you weekly motivational videos for support and mindset strategies to identify and overcome self-limiting beliefs that could be holding you back from having the CONFIDENCE and BODY you want. 🌠

Drop a 🎃 in the comments below and TAG your workout buddy if you’re ready to get Fit for Fall! 🍁🌞🍂👇

How do you sign up?? Head to the Link in my bio!!! 😘 #tbgstrong

node.text:
Do you find yourself reminiscing about moments in life before they’re actually over?

I found myself talking about Summer in a past tense last week as if it was already “over” 😱And yet, here we are still in the middle of August with plenty of time to enjoy all the flavors and fun summer has to offer 🍹

👉🏼I promised myself at the beginning of quarantine that I would take some time to enjoy the little things, and not rush through life so much as I used to do👈🏼

Don’t get me wrong, we need things to look forward to, goals to achieve ⭐️, and dreams to work toward. But, we also need to take time and enjoy the present moment 🧘‍♂️

I’m asking you right now, what is one goal you still want to achieve before summer comes to a close? You still have time to change your eating habits, read that book, go run that 5k, or spend more time with family 🏖🌻🏃🏼‍♀️💕

🍒🍉Join me, and download my 28-Day at home workout and meal plan to really make the most of these last few weeks of summer! I can help you achieve those summer goals, and have fun while doing it! 🍑🍍

☀️ Summer isn’t over yet ☀️

Download Stronger Summer today.

💥 Link in Bio.

#tbgstrongersummer #summerisntoveryet #getstrong #tbgstrong #workoutplan #mealplan #enjoylife

node.text:
Groceries can be EXPENSIVE! And I found that most the time I was throwing away food or buying ingredients I already had! And not to mention, every time I opened my fridge I felt overwhelmed with WHAT I COULD make for a healthy meal... So, I decided to take charge and organize my fridge and freezer so that I could support my health goals, reduce stress (an organized room is an organized mind!) and save time and money on my groceries!

Check out this video to see how I organize my fridge and freezer and make healthy simple.

Happy Sunday IG Fam! If you’ve seen my stories you know that I’ve been dealing with this crazy rash/hives for the past 2.5 weeks. 😩

My doctor said my body is having a major inflammatory response from the chemical exposure to my eyes 4 weeks ago. And this is making me EXTREMELY sensitive to any fragrances, sulfates (found in laundry detergent, shampoos, deli meat and wine 😭 to name a few).

I’ve spent this weekend doing a MASS CLEAN + re-washing all my bedding, clothes, towels, etc… and going through all my beauty products to try and eliminate all things that may be contributing to this flare up.

I also have been experimenting with making my own beauty scrubs with all natural ingredients (like coffee grounds, coconut oil, etc..)which have helped a TON.🙏

I’m thinking about doing a full workshop on how to make these food-based body scrubs on my @amazonlive channel this week. 💝Lemme know in the comments if that sounds interesting to you!👇👇

Ps- swipe to see how excited Chucky was to go on a walk this morning!

They advice I would give to myself for my next pregnancy?

To just f*cking OWN it.

To own the journey.

To own the changes, as they are only temporary.

To own the beauty of our bodies as it grows another life.

Because growth is necessary for change to occur.

And sometimes we are left with marks and scars as a friendly reminder of what we accomplished.

And that deserves to be celebrated.

So fix your hair, put on some Britney and go OWN today.
✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨

Miles and I have had some wonderful conversations lately about our future, and what that looks like for us as we think about expanding our family. While that might not be in the cards for a while, as Andara holds the key to our hearts right now, I would be lying if I said I didn't see more kids in our future. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
With Modern Fertility, women can use their hormone test to determine if you have more or fewer eggs than average, what you could expect from IVF or egg freezing, how your hormone levels compare to the average, and just a general status of your hormone health!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Modern Fertility is the first comprehensive fertility hormone test for women that you can take at home. I know we all have our own goals, plans, and dreams, but did you know that 1 in 6 couples has trouble conceiving? We have all the tools to prevent pregnancy but we need more information to help us plan for it (even if kids are in the far future)! I will be taking this test once I am done nursing Andara, and I will be sharing the results with you all :) I seriously encourage you to take this test and learn more about your body, and plan for your future ladies! Whether you want kids now, in the future, or at all, it is a great way to get a check on your hormones and empower you to make your own decisions. I know it will really help Miles and me as we navigate this beautiful life we are building together <3
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⭐️ Make sure you use my link for $20 off your first test: http://modernfertility.com/krystal

🎆 I hope everyone had a safe holiday weekend. In honor of Independence Day, we really took it to heart this year, taking time to really talk about the life we want to create. Freedom should not be taken for granted, and we realized that this year as we grow into our roles as new parents. The free time we used to have isn’t there anymore, so we are learning to adapt and plan for a bright future!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I have identified a major way that I’ve been leaking time and energy, which is that I didn’t have a structured schedule. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
📆 I am transitioning to a digital calendar where I can really plan out my day and week, because my favorite quote is “what we measure we can manage”. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Taking the time to MANAGE my time will allow me to show up more for myself, my family, my business, and my dreams. 🎇 🎆 🎇 I will be sharing how I’m doing this in stories this whole week so follow along if you’re interested. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Speaking of that, we are looking to book a family vacation with the family because we really need one 😅 LOL. We have done one trip with Andara so far, but does anyone have any family-friendly vacation spots you can share with us?! Appreciate any hashtags or tags for spots you recommend!! We are so excited to get away for a family vacation this summer! ☀️ ps. Swipe to see how BIG Andara is getting!! Do you think she looks more like me or her daddy?

node.text:
The past few weeks have been rough. If you saw my stories last week you’d know that I was in and out of doctors appointments to try and figure out what was going on with my eyes. My vision was blurry, my eyes were insanely scratchy/ itchy, bloodshot and non-stop weeping. Five doctors later, it turns out it was a chemical exposure from getting my hair done. It was defeating, upsetting and from pushing off big projects to drastically affected my milk supply, it impacted my life in every way. While it was a total accident, I can’t help but feel soooooo extremely upset.

What I didn’t share as openly was the 10ish days before that incident- when I felt a major drop in my hormones and the overwhelming wave of “figuring out this new life and new version of me” kicked in, hard. The struggles have been “oh-so-real” and while I love my family and being a mommy- it’s fucking hard.

I’ve realized the first step in making changes is acknowledging where you are and asking for help. So I want to let you all know- Moms, especially new moms, NEED help. We may put on makeup and a brave face but there are very real hormonal changes happening in our bodies. There is a confusing cocktail of mourning the freedom we no longer have while discovering that layers and complexities of this new role and identity.

While I wouldn’t say I’m experiencing “postpartum depression” yet… if I continue on without asking for help, support and most importantly sharing what’s on my heart, it will most certainly become that. So please check in on your mom friends or drop a #momtip below. We moms need to stick together. 💗
